<body>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b><i>About:</i></b></span><span class="s2"><i> This article is for a fictional writing app called Scribbler and includes Information Architecture.</i></span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><b><i>Content model:</i></b></span><span class="s2"><i> HC How to / About</i></span></p>
<h1 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 6.0px 0.0px; font: 24.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">How to Set up Bulletin Board view in Scribbler</span></h1>
<p class="p3"><span class="s2">Scribbler's Bulletin Board is a visual outlining tool to help you organize and restructure writing projects by displaying each document as an index card. This gives you an overview of project structure. This guide covers how to enable Bulletin Board view, customize outlining notecards, and use organizational features to improve your workflow.</span></p>
<h2 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">How to Enable Bulletin Board view</span></h2>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Open your Scribbler project</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Go to the </span><span class="s4"><b>Binder</b></span><span class="s2"> document list in the left sidebar &gt; Click on a folder</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Choose one of three ways to view the Bulletin Board:</span></li>
  <ul class="ul1">
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the Menu bar, click </span><span class="s4"><b>View</b></span><span class="s2"> &gt; </span><span class="s4"><b>Bulletin Board</b><b></b></span></li>
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the toolbar, click the </span><span class="s4"><b>Bulletin Board</b></span><span class="s2"> icon</span></li>
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Use the keyboard shortcut </span><span class="s4"><b>Cmd+2</b></span><span class="s2"> (Mac) or </span><span class="s4"><b>Ctrl+2</b></span><span class="s2"> (Windows)</span></li>
  </ul>
</ol>
<h2 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">How to Add Card Details for Discoverability</span></h2>
<p class="p3"><span class="s2">Card labels, status tags, and custom metadata can help you track your project section's progress.</span></p>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Add a Label</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To the left on the Toolbar, go to </span><span class="s4"><b>Inspector &gt; click Tag</b></span><span class="s2"> [icon]</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Find the </span><span class="s4"><b>Labels</b></span><span class="s2"> dropdown menu</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Select from: No Label, Red, Orange, Yellow, Green, Blue, or Purple</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="p3"><span class="s5"><b>Tip:</b></span><span class="s6"> You define the categories you use for each color (for example, yellow cards are flashbacks and red are present day).</span></p>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Add a Status</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To the left on the Toolbar, go to </span><span class="s4"><b>Inspector &gt; Tag</b><b></b></span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Find the </span><span class="s4"><b>Status</b></span><span class="s2"> dropdown menu</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Select from: No Status, To Do, In Progress, First Draft, Revised Draft, Final Draft, or Done</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Set Up Custom Metadata</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To the left on the Toolbar, go to </span><span class="s4"><b>Inspector &gt; click Tag</b></span><span class="s2"> [icon]</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Below the Status section, click the </span><span class="s4"><b>Set Up Custom Metadata</b></span><span class="s2"> button</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Click the </span><span class="s4"><b>+</b></span><span class="s2"> button to add a new metadata field</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Type a name for your metadata field</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Configure the field settings:</span></li>
  <ul class="ul1">
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Type</b></span><span class="s2"> dropdown menu, select the metadata type: </span><span class="s4"><b>Text</b></span><span class="s2">, </span><span class="s4"><b>List</b></span><span class="s2">, or </span><span class="s4"><b>Date</b><b></b></span></li>
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Alignment</b></span><span class="s2"> dropdown menu, select the text alignment: </span><span class="s4"><b>Left</b></span><span class="s2">, </span><span class="s4"><b>Center</b></span><span class="s2">, or </span><span class="s4"><b>Right</b><b></b></span></li>
  </ul>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To delete a metadata field, click the </span><span class="s4"><b>-</b></span><span class="s2"> button next to it</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">When finished, click </span><span class="s4"><b>OK</b></span><span class="s2"> to save your changes</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="p3"><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Bulletin Board Options</b></span><span class="s2"> view you can customize how your notecards appear to improve your organization.</span></p>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Customize Card Size</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li7"><span class="s7"></span><span class="s8">In the menu, go to </span><span class="s2"><b>View &gt; Bulletin Board Options &gt; Customize Cards</b><b></b></span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Card Size</b></span><span class="s2"> section, use the slider to adjust size: </span><span class="s4"><b>Small</b></span><span class="s2">, </span><span class="s4"><b>Medium</b></span><span class="s2">, or </span><span class="s4"><b>Large</b><b></b></span></li>
</ol>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Customize Font Settings</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Card Menu Setting</b></span><span class="s2"> box, go to the </span><span class="s4"><b>Font</b></span><span class="s2"> section</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Select options from the dropdown menus for </span><span class="s4"><b>font name</b></span><span class="s2">, </span><span class="s4"><b>weight</b></span><span class="s2">, </span><span class="s4"><b>size</b></span><span class="s2">, and </span><span class="s4"><b>character style</b><b></b></span></li>
</ol>
<h3 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 14.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Customize Card Colors</span></h3>
<ol class="ol1">
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">In the </span><span class="s4"><b>Card Menu Setting</b></span><span class="s2"> box, go to the </span><span class="s4"><b>Color</b></span><span class="s2"> section</span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Find the </span><span class="s4"><b>Content Type</b></span><span class="s2"> dropdown menu</span></li>
  <li class="li7"><span class="s7"></span><span class="s8">Select </span><span class="s2"><b>document status</b></span><span class="s8">, </span><span class="s2"><b>label</b></span><span class="s8">, or </span><span class="s2"><b>custom metadata</b><b></b></span></li>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Choose which color to customize for the selected content type:</span></li>
  <ul class="ul1">
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To change text color: Click </span><span class="s4"><b>Text Color</b></span><span class="s2"> &gt; Select a color from the available options</span></li>
    <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">To change background color: Click </span><span class="s4"><b>Background Color</b></span><span class="s2"> &gt; Select a color from the available options</span></li>
  </ul>
  <li class="li5"><span class="s3"></span><span class="s2">Repeat steps 3–4 to set colors for each content type (document status, label, and custom metadata can each have their own text and background colors)</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="p3"><span class="s5"><b>Tip:</b></span><span class="s6"> To change the card color, you must already have added a Document Status, Label, or Custom Metadata to that card.</span></p>
<h2 style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 18.0px 'Helvetica Neue'; color: #1d1c20; -webkit-text-stroke: #1d1c20"><span class="s2">Related resources</span></h2>
